first_reading.text:
[[Si 44,1]]Now will I praise those godly men, our ancestors, each in his own time.
[[Si 44,9]]But of others there is no memory, for when they ceased, they ceased. And they are as though they had not lived, they and their children after them.
[[Si 44,10]]Yet these also were godly men whose virtues have not been forgotten;
[[Si 44,11]]Their wealth remains in their families, their heritage with their descendants;
[[Si 44,12]]Through God's covenant with them their family endures, their posterity, for their sake.
[[Si 44,13]]And for all time their progeny will endure, their glory will never be blotted out;
